snippet.textDisplay:
Something I noticed while watching this...To understand it you will have to go check out the infamous Tony Royster Jr drum solo when he was 12 years old. It hit the internet about 15 years ago and at the time was one of my favorite videos to watch. Many of the rhythms and patterns Tony does in his solo are seen in this video performed by Neil which would indicate that Tony was inspired by Neil (no surprise)… however some of these clips were taken much more recent than 15 years ago which would indicate that, perhaps, Neil got some inspiration from a young Tony Royster Jr as well?

Either that or their styles are coincidentally very similar.

snippet.textDisplay:
Rush brought me decades of enjoyment. Whether it was falling asleep to the Necromancer , listening to drum solo playlists at work , jogging to tunes like marathon and big money , or just putting on the headphones and tuning out the world while tuning into albums like hold your fire , permanent waves , and counterparts .

No band has ever captivated me like Rush and I felt like I lost a life time friend when Neil passed . R.I.P

Neil for sure was the best drummer ever! RIP Neil.

snippet.textDisplay: All The Worlds A Stage one of the greatest live albums of all time. The title of the album alludes to William Shakespeare's play As You Like It, which would again be referenced by Rush in their 1981 song "Limelight".  for me I played that album along with "if you want blood" & "Unleashed in the east". Those albums captured the excitement of what was happening at the shows and as a young teenager when those albums came out I knew I had to be there and see this excitement for myself. Saw Rush for the first time headline the Texas Jam 1984, been a huge fan since 2112 came out. I call Rush cerebral music because it's like a very heady sativa high, written by a very mature cerebral intelligent group of guys. This is a devistating blow. Will be playing only rush in my car for quite a while. So many great songs my favorite is probably The Temple Of Syrinx. Crank it up loud as fuck people. Will be playing Rush till the day I die. RIP Professor.
